gw.api.webservice.pc.productmodel

Interface IProductModelAPI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.guidewire.pl.system.service.Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ProductModelAPIImpl

    public interface IProductModelAPI
extends com.guidewire.pl.system.service.Service
    Provides service API methods for modifying the PolicyCenter product model. For the web service implementation, look at the gosu implementation gw.webservice.pc.productmodel.ProductModelAPI Modifying the Product Model definition has three major prerequisites:

    1. User must have permission - only an administrator may make modifications to the product model
    2. Server must not be in dev mode - the environment property gw.server.mode must be "dev"
    3. Server must be in maintenance mode - put the server in this mode before making any of the modification calls.

    Author:
    Allan Heydon, Victor Tso

    • Method Detail

      • synchronizeProductModel

        void synchronizeProductModel()
                      throws java.io.IOException,
                             com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.TransactionException
        Synchronizes the contents of the database's product model to the contents of the server's XML configuration. This is important to call in order to relay implicit delete information to the database after a sync to source control or hand-edits of the XML.
        Throws:
        ServerStateException - If the server is not in maintenance mode or is not in dev mode.
        SOAPServerException - If the user does not have permission to access this functionality or an error occurs while doing the synchronization.
        java.io.IOException
        com.guidewire.pl.system.exception.TransactionException

      • synchronizeSystemTables

        void synchronizeSystemTables()
                      throws SOAPServerException
        Synchronizes the contents of the database's system tables to the contents of the server's XML configuration. This is important to call in order to relay implicit delete information to the database after a sync to source control or hand-edits of the XML.
        Throws:
        ServerStateException - If the server is not in maintenance mode or is not in dev mode.
        SOAPServerException - If the user does not have permission to access this functionality or an error occurs while doing the synchronization.
